<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-659-781  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 659 781.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  Dec 4 1990 v4 n41 p32(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Coastal Associates Publishing L.P. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Image Club's Evolution converts Type 3 PostScript fonts to Type 1.andO;(Image Club Graphics Inc.'s printer software) (productannouncement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>McManus, Neil.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Image Club Graphics Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   PostScript (Printer software) (Computer programs)Evolution (Add-in/on software) (Product introduction).andO;Topic:     FontsProduct IntroductionPrinter Software.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Neil McManusandM;Calgary, Alberta -- Image Club Graphics Inc. last month shipped Evolution, autility that converts PostScript fonts from Type 1 to Type 3 format and viceversa.andM;The $99 program, which competes with Altsys Corp.'s $149 Metamorphosis, alsoconverts both font types into PostScript outlines that can be manipulatedwith such programs as Aldus FreeHand and Adobe Illustrator.andM;Jeff Papa at Phillip Gary Design of St. Petersburg, Fla., uses Evolution tomanipulate font outlines in Adobe Illustrator when preparing advertising workfor such clients as Great Explorations, a nearby children's museum.andM;One benefit of Evolution, Papa said, is that PostScript fonts converted toType 1 can be displayed on-screen by Adobe Type Manager.andP;  &quot;A lot of our oldType 3 fonts wouldn't work with ATM, and that was a drag.andP;  They looked reallycheesy on the screen before we bought Evolution and converted them to Type1,&quot; he said.andM;Evolution does not support all font formats, but an Image Club spokesman saidthe company is still updating the program.andP;  As of Version 1.02, Evolutiondoes not convert fonts in Altsys' Fontographer or Letraset's FontStudioformats.andP;  The program also conflicts with some Startup documents, includingolder versions of QuickINIT from CE Software Inc.'s QuickMail package.andM;Image Club Graphics Inc. is at 1902 11th St. S.E., Suite 5, Calgary, Alberta,Canada T2G 3G2.andP;  Phone (403) 262-8008; fax (403) 261-7013.andO;</TEXT></DOC>